28326691.name: Dice Throw
28326691.instructions:
‚òÖ‚òÖ Dice Throw ‚òÖ‚òÖ  

I HIGHLY recommend you play this on TurboWarp. 
https://turbowarp.org/723902827. Also, for the best experience, go into full screen and zoom in so that the gray edges are barely visible. 

You're a cat with a dice, and you knock out enemies by throwing the dice at them. After all the enemies are gone, you proceed to the next wave. Your goal is to finish all the waves.

I worked really hard on this, so if you enjoyed it, leave a like and favorite.

‚Äì‚Äì‚Äì Instructions ‚Äì‚Äì‚Äì                               [Very important]

- Move around with arrow keys or WASD
- Press space to throw the dice at enemies
- The dice will land on a number, and that number will determine the damage and speed of the next attack
- The farther your mouse is away from the character, the faster the throw
- There are six enemies, each one more powerful than the previous one

‚Äì‚Äì‚Äì Enemies ‚Äì‚Äì‚Äì
1. Basic enemy, slow, 1 attack damage
2. Fast enemy, 1 attack damage
3. Very slow enemy, shoots bullets, 1 attack damage
4. Big strong enemy, slow, 2 attack damage
5. Teleportation enemy, teleports when dice is thrown
      [Tip: Get really close to it and throw a 5 or 6 at it.]
6. Creeper. Walks up to you and explodes, fast enemy
7. ?????

‚Äì‚Äì‚Äì Credits ‚Äì‚Äì‚Äì

This was made for @GentleX's contest. I hope it wins, because I worked on it for a month. . .even if it doesn't, I still made a really good game because of that contest.

[UPDATE] This didn't make it into round two. . .at least it made it into round one. I got in the top 80 out of 1400 of entries, so that's good at least.

Also @Toasterboii290 helped me come up with ideas for the enemies before the game was released, which was a big help. 

- The music is Rigor Mormist from plants vs. zombies
- The cat costumes are from @griffpatch_tutor's rpg starter project
- The explosion sound effect is from Minecraft
- And the health bars I made following @griffpatch's tutorial

The rest is be me.

‚Äì‚Äì‚Äì‚Äì‚Äì‚Äì‚Äì‚Äì‚Äì‚Äì‚Äì‚Äì

This is my biggest project up to date, with 2300+ blocks! 2362, to be exact.

70649780.name: StandTestV2
70649780.instructions:
Instructions:

Note: This game contains
blood and swears. (Can be turned off in the
settings, the blood is the only
one enabled by default)

If there are any bugs, click the green flag again.

Controls

A - Move left

D - Move Right

H - Summon Stand

L - Enter Cheat Code

The rest of the controls can be seen at the top right corner. Most moves use keys such as e, r, t, y, g, x, and z

Moveset of Stands (and a brief description of the move):

„ÄåThe World„Äç

E - Barrage - a set of fast punches

R - Heavy Punch - one powerful punch forward

T - Knives - throw knives in the direction of your mouse cursor

G - Donut - punch your fist through their stomach, making them a "donut"

Z - Time Movement - stop time and move forward, this is seen as "teleporting" for others

Space - Stop time - Unleash the power of „ÄåThe World„Äç and stop time for a maximum of five seconds, any damage done during this stopped time will be delt after time is resumed

„ÄåKing Crimson„Äç

E - Barrage - a set of fast punches

R - Heavy Punch - one powerful punch forward

T - Blood Blind - blind the enemy with your own blood and make it so they are unable to see and cannot walk

G - Donut V2 - Similar to the first donut, punch a hole through their stomach causing them to take massive amounts of damage

Y - Chop - swiftly thrust your hand down on them

Z - Epitaph - briefly see into the future and what the dummy is going to do next (If the dummy is unable to move, epitaph will not activate)

X - Time Skip - time is skipped for a brief moment, acts as a "teleport"

Space - Time Erase - while active time is erased and you are unable to be touched or damaged but you can also not touch anything, while in erased time you can see all of the future movements being made, the only move that can be used offensively in time erase is blood blind because once the blood leaves your body it is not part of you anymore therefore causing damage

„ÄåThe Hand„Äç

E - Barrage - a set of fast punches

R - Heavy Punch - one powerful punch forward

T - Pull - erase space in front of you causing reality to fix itself and the dummy coming towards you

Y - Erase - erase the space in front of you and causing deadly injuries to the dummy

Z - Acceleration - erase the space in front of you causing you to move forward as a result

„ÄåFuecoco„Äç (pokemon)

E - Scream - Make the dummy's ears bleed

R - Punch - Dash behind the dummy and punch him (mini beatdown)

T - Spin - Rotate the dummy

G - Explosion - Summon an explosion of Fuecoco at your mouse pointer and damage the dummy

Space - Launch a missile that will follow your mouse pointer, does deadly amounts of damage to the dummy

„ÄåCockatoo„Äç

E - haha - Bird does a scream

R - Amongus - Turns dummy into amogus

T - Bite - Cockatoo quickly dashes over to the dummy and bites him

Y - Pilot - Allows you to control the Cockatoo, can be toggled

„ÄåScythe„Äç (Secret stand, you have to find it!)

Blade Damage - Passive - When the dummy touches the blade of the scythe, damage is delt

E - üíÄ - Wear a skull

R - Throw - Throw your scythe to the mouse pointer and watch it spin

T - Dash - Quickly move forward

G - A World of Darkness - Makes it so your blade does 2x damage in the dark

X - D E A T H

„ÄåChoker„Äç

Electricicity Bar - Passive - Drains when energy is used

E - Barrage - a set of fast punches

R - Heavy Punch - one powerful punch forward

T - Eletric Imbued Punch - Punches forward with electricity, if your punch hits the dumym then he will be electrocuted

Click and Drag (click on the backdrop) - Eletric spikes will form at your mouse pointer, drag to change the size of them, the bigger the size the more energy they will use and more damage delt

Z - Requiem - Use the Requiem arrow and obtain „ÄåChoker Requiem„Äç

„ÄåChoker Requiem„Äç

Requiem - Passive - Do unusual amounts of damage and have a larger range (you do more damage and its easier to hit attacks)

E - Barrage - a set of fast punches

R - Heavy Punch - one powerful punch forward

T - Soul Grab - Punch towards the dummy and knock his soul out of him, watch as his soul will be crushed to nothing and kill him

Y - Energy Beam - Thrust a beam of energy towards your mouse pointer

Z - Time Shall Slow - Use electricity on your body to such an extensive amount that time starts to slow around you

Space - Infinite Energy - Move behind the dummy and punch him with an unimaginable amount of energy

„ÄåCacatua„Äç

E - Poop - Poop on the ground

R - Peck - Reach out and peck the dummy

T - Stomp - Squish the dummy

Y - Flap - Blow the dummy away

Z - Scream - AAAAA, AAAAAA, AAAAA




StandTestV2 is a remake of my older game "Stand Test". In this newer game almost every mechanic will be remade. 

Link for old game:
https://scratch.mit.edu/projects/792002424/

Both of these games are based on an anime/manga called "Jojo's Bizarre Adventure" by Hirohiko Araki.



(This game is still being worked on)
